6 An Act relating to child care; amending 10 O.S. 2021,
6 Section 405.4, which relates to education and
7 continuing education requirements; extending
7 continuing education cycle; requiring certain
8 certificate for child care facility personnel within
8 specified time frame; requiring infant safe sleep
9 training for certain individuals; and providing an
9 effective date.
10
10
11
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 10 O.S. 2021, Section 405.4, is
13
14 amended to read as follows:
14
15 Section 405.4. A. Any person with a bachelor’s degree or
15
16 postgraduate degree shall be considered as having met the
16
17 educational requirements for a director of a full-time child care
17
18 center required by the Department of Human Services. Nothing in
18
19 this section shall be construed as to affect annual continuing
19
20 education requirements. The director of a child care center may
20
21 also qualify as a master teacher for children of all ages.
21
22 B. Any person replacing a master teacher at a child care center
22
23 shall be granted a one-year probationary period to fulfill the
23
24 educational qualifications required by the Department for a master
24
Req. No. 744 Page 1
1 teac her. The Department may extend the probationary period an
1
2 additional year as long as the person is actively pursuing that
2
3 goal.
3
4 C. 1. Prior to or within twelve (12) months of employment,
4
5 teaching personnel of child care facilities shall obtain and
5
6 maintain a current Oklahoma Professional Development Ladder (OPDL)
6
7 certificate as provided by rules promulgated by the Director of
7
8 Human Services.
8
9 2. Renewals and training for OPDL certification and any other
9
10 professional development or continuing education required by the
10
11 Department for child care facility personnel shall be on a two-year
11
12 cycle.
12
13 3. Infant safe sleep training shall be required every two (2)
13
14 years for any individual working with infants under one (1) year of
14
15 age.
15
16 D. Licensed child care facilities opened or expanded before
16
17 November 1, 2016, shall have thirty-five (35) square feet of floor
17
18 area per infant in rooms occupied only by infants. New construction
18
19 and existing space not previously licensed for child care after
19
20 November 1, 2016, shall have forty (40) square feet of floor area
20
21 per infant in rooms occupied only by infants.
21
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
